text: Lia Leismüller (29 March 1931 - 6 December 2001) was a German alpine skier. She competed in the women's downhill at the 1952 Winter Olympics. ==References== Category:1931 births Category:2001 deaths Category:German female alpine skiers Category:Olympic alpine skiers of Germany Category:Alpine skiers at the 1952 Winter Olympics Category:Sportspeople from Garmisch- Partenkirchen
